      • getConstant

        public DfaTypeValue getConstant(java.lang.Object value,
                                PsiType type)
        Creates a constant of given type and given value. Constants are always unique (two different constants are not equal to each other). The following types of the objects are supported:
        • Integer/Long/Double/Float/Boolean (will be unboxed)
        • Character/Byte/Short (will be unboxed and widened to int)
        • String
        • PsiEnumConstant (enum constant value, type must be the corresponding enum type)
        • PsiField (a final field that contains a unique value, type must be a type of that field)
        • PsiType (java.lang.Class object value, type must be java.lang.Class)
        Parameters:
        type - type of the constant
        Returns:
        a DfaTypeValue whose type is DfConstantType that corresponds to given constant.

      • getConstantFromVariable

        public DfaValue getConstantFromVariable(PsiVariable variable)
        Parameters:
        variable - variable to create a constant based on its value
        Returns:
        a value that represents a constant created from variable; null if variable cannot be represented as a constant
